/sta13hb1041a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-02-02T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "S", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/sen14.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 18598, "bill_version_id": 99125, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "2004-01-10T16:22:21-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to revise how the sales tax applies to certain payments regarding property leased between members of a controlled group. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That \u00a7 10-45-20.1 be amended to read as follows: 10-45-20.1. Payments made by one member of the controlled group to another member of a controlled group which represent an allocation, reimbursement , or charge for services provided by or rendered by the members of the controlled group are specifically exempted from the provisions of this chapter and the computation of the tax imposed by it. The exemption provided in this section does not apply to the lease of tangible personal property unless the sales or use tax has been paid on the property by the lessor. Section 2. That \u00a7 10-45-20.5 be amended to read as follows: 10-45-20.5. There are specifically exempted from the provisions of this chapter and the computation of the tax imposed by it, gross receipts from the sale of services rendered by a related corporation as defined in subdivision 10-43-1(11) for use by a financial institution as defined in subdivision 10-43-1(4) or on any service rendered by a financial institution as defined in subdivision 10-43-1(4) for use by a related corporation as defined in subdivision 10-43-1(11). For the purposes of this section, the term, related corporation, includes a corporation which together with the financial institution is part of a controlled group of corporations as defined in 26 U.S.C. \u00a7 1563 as in effect on January 1, 1989, except that the eighty percent ownership requirements set forth in 26 U.S.C. \u00a7 1563(a)(2)(A) for a brother-sister controlled group are reduced to fifty-one percent. The exemption provided in this section does not apply to the lease of tangible personal property unless the sales or use tax has been paid on the property by the lessor."}, {"bill_id": 18598, "bill_version_id": 100481, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2004-02-03T08:50:06-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 18598, "action_date": "2004-01-13T12:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 99180, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/99180.pdf", "status_text": "First read in House and referred to", "journal_page": 24, "committee_id_action": 831, "committee_id_assigned": 827, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 18598, "action_date": "2004-01-20T07:45:00-06:00", "document_id": 99351, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/99351.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date", "journal_page": null, "committee_id_action": 827, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 18598, "action_date": "2004-01-20T07:45:00-06:00", "document_id": 99351, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/99351.pdf", "status_text": "Do Pass,", "journal_page": 111, "committee_id_action": 827, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "P", "vote": {"vote_id": 57119, "president_vote": null, "Yea": [3057, 3073, 3078, 3085, 3088, 3100, 3102, 3110, 3127, 3140, 3142, 3143, 3147, 3148], "Excused": [3095]}}, {"bill_id": 18598, "action_date": "2004-01-20T07:45:00-06:00", "document_id": 99351, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/99351.pdf", "status_text": "Place on Consent Calendar", "journal_page": null, "committee_id_action": 827, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 18598, "action_date": "2004-01-21T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 99482, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdle